  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/5233",
  "title": "`getServerState` doesn't correctly handle exceptions and crashes entire node server",
  "body": "## 🐛 Bug description\r\n\r\n`getServerState` doesn't correctly handle exceptions in search client (e.g. `ECONNREFUSED`), which causes it to hang forever, and crashes the entire node server if there's no defined handler for `'unhandledRejection'`.\r\n\r\n## 🔍 Bug reproduction\r\n\r\n**Live reproduction:**\r\n\r\nThis is the minimal Remix reproduction:\r\n\r\nhttps://stackblitz.com/edit/node-vn7ere?file=app/entry.server.tsx\r\n\r\nSteps to test:\r\n\r\n1. Run the StackBlitz WebContainer - it should crash\r\n2. Uncomment code in `app/entry.server.tsx`, which defines `process.on('unhandledRejection', ...)` handler and restart everything. Now the server should not crash, but `getServerState` will still hang forever\r\n3. The workaround is to add `Promise.race`: see `index.tsx`\r\n\r\nNote that this bug is not specific to Remix - I was able to reproduce it in Next as well.\r\n\r\n## 💭 Expected behavior\r\n\r\n`getServerState` should correctly propagate exceptions so that they can be catched. `unhandledRejection` handler should not be required.\r\n\r\n<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->\r\n\r\n## 🖥 Screenshots\r\n\r\n<!-- If applicable, add screenshots to help explain your problem. -->\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n- React InstantSearch Hooks version: [6.38.1]\r\n- React version: [e.g. 17.0.2]\r\n- Browser: [N/A]\r\n- OS: [Linux]\r\n- Node version: v16.14.2 and v18.12.0\r\n",
